item.title: Getting server public
item.dc:creator: @Tech_Python Tech Python
item.description:
@Tech_Python wrote:

you can’t just apply your gateway ip to the server and expect it to go public, you need to add a 43594 in your firewall exceptions, portforward the port, in: 43594 out: 43594 and you need a no-ip running off your port, i suggest making a webclient and buying a vps… so much easier and your server is online 24/7 and they do portforwarding for you… all you need to do is sit back and relax.
